The <a href="javascript:card_browser(242)">Summit of Amon Hen</a>    </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Strategy</Font></TD><TD> </TD></TR><TR><TD COLSPAN="2" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="bfont"> This deck reminds me of one deck which was back then very famous : the &quot;Dont Pee In The Twilight Pool&quot; deck. However, this deck utilizes boromir as a sure pump up for frodo. Anyway, here&#39;s how its suppose to work. This deck is a choke deck, combined with a deadly shadow of moria swarm. The idea is to get your opponent clogged up his hands with shadow cards, thus slowing down his set up for a god-like fellowship, and enabling you to swarm him at site 5-7. The startegy that&#39;s with Boromir is exactly the same as the movie as he&#39;s gonna die at site 9. :p <br>
<br>
Hear me explain then.<br>
<br>
Bid: bid low, you wouldnt mind going second. maybe 1 would do the trick.<br>
<br>
site 1: east road. This is huge for your shadow as it might help to clear up your hands for you to reach for that shards of narsil if it hasnt arrive on the scene in the first draw. it gives extra twilight<br>
<br>
site 2: if you move second, this site will help you to draw more cards. remember that in case shards comes out early game, and you have boromir in hand, stack him there together with some of your other unneeded stuffs.<br>
<br>
site 3: this is a choke deck. :p thus, try preventing from giving him too much twilights!! its wise to just give 1-3 at most 4 twilights from site 1-3.<br>
<br>
site 4: well, this will help your orcs get back their weapons for just 1 twilight. cheap and effective i&#39;d say if you already have your armories out.<br>
<br>
site 5: try go for a swarm... sometimes balrog can be a real mess here... u can also use him to bring out more minions which can add twilights or so.<br>
<br>
site 6: also try go for a swarm here... play the first runner at dimrill dale and you&#39;ll get +2 twilight free!!<br>
<br>
site 7: yet again, another chance for swarming.<br>
<br>
site 8: the shores will stop your opponent from moving 7-9. and here&#39;s where you&#39;d wanna show boromir&#39;s macho-ness!! :p<br>
<br>
site 9: if you cant swarm your opponent by 7. you should at least be at 8, and pull out boromir during your fellowship. make gosh darnit sure your frodo and bounder has no wounds, or maybe frodo with just 2 wounds max. it doesnt matter abt twilights anymore already when you reach this stage. at 9, solve frodo&#39;s skirmish first. pump him up with dagger strike (if any) and then with boro&#39;s ability, exert bounder so that he wont be overwhelmed unless x3. HUGE. I&#39;d say that will make Frodo Str. (6+2+3+3)=14. Overwhelm him? You&#39;d need 42!!<br>
<br>
NOTE:<br>
The trick here is when to conserve your cards and when not to. Take note that this deck is relatively slim for a moria ditching card style. So its all up to your own experience in playing.<br>
<br>
Aragon is HUGE, try not to put down all your weapons at once if facing nazguls coz Cantea is very irritating. In anyway, most of the time, you&#39;ll be only giving a very small amount of twilight which makes it only possible for shadow players to pull a minion on you. Even Tropp will fall prey to still sharp. Balrog? kill him off with all the damage +1 +1 +1 +1 :)<br>
ROTN is like a one shot to go hero. Exert him to take on guys and kill them off! Trust me, Uruks wont be able to out pump Aragorn in this deck.<br>
<br>
Pros:<br>
Good choke against Sauron and Uruks.<br>
Isengard Orcs stands no chance against this deck. All the damages the orcs suck will leave your opponents face look pale! Nazguls also can be chopped down most of the time. Just be careful of Breaths. <br>
<br>
Cons:<br>
Moria swarm...hmm... some problem here... since you wont be able to choke them that much either. Anyway, Gorn can take out many nasty minions too... you just have to exert him more. Then heal with athelas.<br>
<br>
